  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The logged-out front page of the redesigned site, and the logged-in landing
page, both show a link to events.openhatch.org. Right now, that site is down.

We should either:

1) Remove the link from the redesigned front page, or

2) Make a page that explains our events, and point the link there.

I'm a fan of option 2, but it's worth considering what we can do that would let
us ship the redesign faster. It could be as simple as writing a wiki page, or a
simple static page styled the same as the main site.

(This bug is about the redesign of the site that is occurring during 0.12.02.
You can see that redesign in process, temporarily, here:
<a href="http://gentle-robot-6466.herokuapp.com/">http://gentle-robot-6466.herokuapp.com/</a> )</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
